s=title> Priest of Discord is the Solution</span><hr size=1> Priest of Discord is the solution<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Hail, I come to you in OOC, Verant is again changing the way we play PVP. They said the changes they were considering would make some people unhappy. This could be the purists (like the Darklight Brigade) or the Crossteamers. After brooding for a while, I had an idea, a Win Win situation for the whole server. IF you like my idea, spread it, get the word out. Im truly scared of what they might do this time. Please let them know your feelings about any changes they might make.<br>
<br>
I was thinking today about Verant saying that they are looking to change the way PVP works again. I was grumbling that no matter what they do, a large group of people will be unhappy. Then I hit on an Idea. <br>
When we all start this life in Norrath, we get a Concordance of Discord. Now on a teams PVP server, you destroy it, turn in your guild note, and get to crushing rats, moss snakes and decaying skeletons. What if turning in the book actually did something useful? How about if you turn in your book you become part of the 5th team on a teams PVP server?<br>
Anyone who doesn't turn in a book is restricted to grouping, and buffing their team only. If you turn in your book, your name tag changes color to the new 5th team, and you can hit or be hit by anyone in your range. Keep the code that lets AOE damage not hit those you are grouped with. <br>
I think of any faults in this, other than the very low levels who need to share hunting grounds with characters of the same team, But soon everyone would learn to check the color of the name tag.<br>
This seems to be a win win solution for all the types of players (accept those that want to exploit the immortal healing bug). It will allow all the guild to remain the same, and allow a more even playing field in the teams pvp world. And even make a useless NPC finally useful (could even make him a merchant who sells the Concord of Discord, for those higher levels that want to switch)<br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
<br>
Revy L'Oution<br>
